{
  "texts": [
    "Since agentic language is generally perceived as being more hirable than communal language style (Madera et al., 2009 (Madera et al.,, 2019;; Khan et al., 2021), bias in language agency might further lead to biases in hiring decisions.",
    "Understanding and detecting hallucinations in LLMs have become an important problem (Mündler et al., 2023; Ji et al., 2023; Azamfirei et al., 2023).",
    "Previous works on hallucination detection proposed three main types of approaches: Information Extraction-based, Question Answering (QA)-based and Natural Language Inference (NLI)based approaches.",
    "Our study utilizes the NLIbased approach (Kryscinski et al., 2020; Maynez et al., 2020; Laban et al., 2022), which uses the original input as context to determine the entailment with the model-generated text.",
    "To do this, prior works have proposed document-level NLI and sentence-level NLI approaches."
  ]
}